modules.description: Provides optimization algorithms for minimizing or maximizing real-valued functions with bounds and nonlinear constraints. Operates on floating-point numbers, vectors, and user-defined objective functions with gradient support. Used to solve constrained optimization problems in scientific computing and engineering simulations.

This module offers numerical optimization algorithms like MMA, COBYLA, and Nelder-Mead, designed for minimizing or maximizing objective functions with constraints, bounds, and varying gradient requirements. It operates on float arrays for variables and function values, along with callback functions to define constraints and control optimization processes. Use cases include engineering design, parameter fitting, and scenarios requiring gradient-free or constrained optimization with customizable stopping criteria and solver configurations.
